<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-16ADA5CA-E0BB-4DFF-8894-37AC4238E0EB" version="4" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-16ADA5CA-E0BB-4DFF-8894-37AC4238E0EB" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">02 The function of the pressure manifold.</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">A pressure manifold is required to enable choosing which heads to purge. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure manifold consists of an air supply, a valve and air outlet. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The design of the manifold is made in such a way the manifold can be expanded to match with the amount of printheads. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure manifold is designed for pressure from -15 mbar to 250 mbar. The pressure manifolds are electrical, controlled. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Definition</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A pressure manifold is required to enable choosing which heads to purge. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A pressure manifold consists of an air supply, a valve and air outlet. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure manifold is designed in such a way that the manifold can be expanded to match with the amount of printheads. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Furthermore the pressure manifold is designed for pressure from -15 mbar to 250 mbar. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure manifolds are electrical controlled. 
</p></li></ul><table id="GUID-25FC27F3-40DA-4CFA-8183-80059A8E9462" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="5.91*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="5.21*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Image 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Most of the time the PH has to be connected to the APSU, and to avoid heat generation in the valve we want the valve to be deactivated in that case. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When a purge-wipe has to be performed the APSU has to provide an over-pressure instead of a vacuum. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Only the printhead(s) that are purged stay connected to the APSU. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printheads that are not purged should be switched off from the APSU to hold their vacuum while the APSU is generating over-pressure for the purge. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Valve activated = voltage supplied to valve = valve closed = no airflow from topside to frontside. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Valve de-activated = no voltage supplied to valve = valve open= air can flow from topside to frontside. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B1E6F4D5-BDF6-4C34-B736-38A41C2895F4" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-C289911C-EAF9-467B-8236-FD2B1FD8F114-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C289911C-EAF9-467B-8236-FD2B1FD8F114-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The single manifold. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5AD9A3B6-217F-44BC-B7F7-75261FD3AA0D" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-34FE1616-4B7C-4324-A0EF-299FE55489B6-low.jpg" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-34FE1616-4B7C-4324-A0EF-299FE55489B6-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Modular pressure manifold. In this picture 3 pressure manifolds are shown. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-2E60C99C-F1CF-4843-91CF-C6620DC4DF2E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-56AE9E3F-09D8-46A0-B721-6558829F543E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-56AE9E3F-09D8-46A0-B721-6558829F543E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="GUID-44CC9D37-524C-4240-A579-9C6FC3D85313" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="8.82*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="7.44*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The pressure manifolds are located on the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is the most efficient location as this enables the use of air supply tube through the IGUS to the carriage. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5CECC760-BFE9-47A1-86CC-0AE6803B65EB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-5DB6499F-EEE4-4D6E-953A-624523D6D87F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5DB6499F-EEE4-4D6E-953A-624523D6D87F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado 1630: Indicated with Red arrow, only 1 passive manifold is used. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-2C5BAEA8-C2A0-4ADE-90B5-DAF6FCD18352" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7F545F1A-0A95-4CFE-B007-C1FA13C1B7C3-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7F545F1A-0A95-4CFE-B007-C1FA13C1B7C3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado 1650: Indicated with Red arrow, only 1 passive manifold is used. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3BFBB0D4-6986-408B-96FD-F0A3CE5A6401" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6DC506DD-2EF3-4A01-A4F7-BBF0BD0E426F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6DC506DD-2EF3-4A01-A4F7-BBF0BD0E426F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado M-series: 3 electrical controlled manifolds are used to generate the spitting purge. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7AF42017-61E6-4C0A-84B6-0EE4CEB3B63E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-70267EA7-BB2F-4728-B441-3F859E1E9EF5-low.jpg" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-70267EA7-BB2F-4728-B441-3F859E1E9EF5-low.jpg"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-FE35F538-1785-4DC7-A246-E1EB5ED33BE7.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
